race.comment: THE TIMES (12) made progress last time out, finishing 2 lengths from the winner in second at the end of 1500m at this track. Suitably placed so anticipating another big run. RARITY POSSE (16) is a four-start maiden who resumed from a spell last start and was beaten 14 lengths when 11th over 1300m at Maronas. Will take a lot from that hit-out and looks a strong chance to break through. INDIO QAIS (8) is facing the starter for the first time. By Brooklyn Boy and comes from the Ercilia Brun stable. Expected to feature. ORGULHO DEL RIO (14) is a three-year-old colt on debut by Emcee from Rubia Del Rio who has in turn produced the winner of a black type. Promising type who is one to keep a close eye on in betting.
